                <h1>TIFF vs PNG: Which Image Format Should You Choose?</h1>
                <p>TIFF and PNG are popular image formats used for different purposes. TIFF (Tagged Image File Format) is ideal for high-quality images and professional printing due to its lossless compression. PNG (Portable Network Graphics), on the other hand, supports transparency and is perfect for web use, offering a good balance of quality and smaller file size. Choose based on your needs!</p>
